# nw_parameters_attribution_t.developer

**Case**

A developer-initiated network request.

## Declaration

```swift
case developer
```

## Discussion

Use this value for the `attribution` parameter of a call to the [doc://com.apple.network/documentation/Network/nw_parameters_get_attribution(_:)] method when creating a network request for any purpose other than when the user explicitly accesses a link. This includes requests that your app makes to get user data. This is the default value.

For cases where the user enters a URL, like in the navigation bar of a web browser, or taps or clicks a URL to load the content it represents, use the [doc://com.apple.network/documentation/Network/nw_parameters_attribution_t/user] value instead.

## Request Sources

- **nw_parameters_attribution_t.user**: The user explicitly directs the app to make a network request.
